<br>
Since according to what I read, pets no longer use either the damage or delay of a weapon if the damage isn't as good as their base un-armed damage.<br>
<br>
When, if ever...should I give my pets summoned weapons?<br>
<br>
I often see Mage pets wielding swords that look like ornate cutlasses. What are these? Did they change the Sword of Runes graphic?<br>
<br>
I'm getting Sword of Runes next level and really want to get the full scoop on giving pets the weapons that we can summon. I have been giving him an Elemental Defender for quite some time because he bashes significantly harder with it.<br>
<br>
Will I still be able to get him to bash with the Elemental Defender if he has two weapons equipped?<br>
<br>
Sorry for so many varying questions, but thanks in advance for the answers. Really digging the mage class so far. Best INT caster class I've tried by far. He's a real box of fire so far at 28, can't wait till later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pyroniousflare>Pyronious Flare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333333>(2/24/03 3:19:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1869.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned Weapons...</span><hr size=1> Should remain a box of fire<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
The cutlass things you see are the Blade of Walnan, 61 spell pet only weap.  As far as the sword of runes...only will help you taking out summoned mobs...procs like a 37 point I think Anti summoned spell.   Used to equip the pet with them all the time during my lvl 50ish hunting sprees in the Hole.<br>
