<br>
It has always been my experience that even after they changed duel welding and delay for pets, there was still a difference when the pet had weapons.  I believe that even though the pet will not hit harder, or faster, I believe the pets ATTACK rating goes up with a weapon.  Higher attack rating means more hits for full damage.<br>
<br>
Do I have experience that showed this?  Yes, way back in the day when I soloed Brownie guards for exp I was VERY bored.  So I paid alot of attention to every stat and tried to play around to see how I could effect the fight.  I tried many fights with a level 57 un-equipped earth pet.  Then started equipping the pet with swords of runes again.  <br>
<br>
While the pet's max hit did not change, nor did his delay, I would swear that he landed MORE hits for HIGHER damage.  I justified this by noticing I needed to nuke less when the pet was equipped.  So with pet weapons I would end the fight at ~80 mana.  With no weapons I would end ~70 mana.<br>
<br>
Have I done anything lately to re-affirm this?  No.  But I'm betting it's still true.  Attack rating normally means the melee will hit harder.  But pets have that nifty melee cap, which they seem to reach easily.  So I think weapons just ups the &quot;average damage per hit.&quot;<br>
<br>
Perhaps, somebody should run some parses and prove/disprove this... <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
